- 2.0.1 | Feb 20 2026:
[Fix] cron.daily rewritten to call APF directly instead of
      /etc/init.d/apf restart; init.d path is broken on systemd-only
      systems (cron.daily)
[Fix] install.sh now sed-replaces /etc/apf in cron.daily when using
      custom INSTALL_PATH (install.sh)
[Fix] apf -u now reports success/failure; previously swallowed all
      output and unconditionally printed "removed" even when host was
      not found in trust system (apf)
[Fix] importconf now preserves glob_allow.rules and glob_deny.rules
      during upgrade; previously only *_hosts.rules were migrated,
      losing curated global allow/deny lists (importconf)
[Change] importconf path references quoted for spaces safety
      (importconf)
[Fix] SSH helper return traffic port range corrected from 513:65535 to
      1024:65535; port 513 is rlogin, modern SSH uses ephemeral ports
      >= 1024 (firewall)
[Fix] --gre-up/--gre-down now acquire mutex_lock before running;
      previously could race with concurrent apf -s or apf -f (apf)
[Fix] sysctl.rules tcp_fack write guarded behind proc file existence;
      removed in kernel 4.15 (sysctl.rules)
[Fix] IPv6 sysctl writes guarded behind proc file existence; prevents
      errors on systems without IPv6 proc entries (sysctl.rules)
[Fix] reserved.networks: added 0.0.0.0/8 "this network" range
      (RFC 1122); commonly spoofed source address (reserved.networks)
[Fix] IP6_NET link-local filter: grep -v fe80 added before head -n1 to
      prevent fe80:: link-local from being selected over global unicast
      address (internals.conf)
[Change] dlist_ecnshame() download validation: entries now validated via
      valid_ip_cidr() during parsing, matching all other dlist download
      functions (functions.apf)
[Fix] Dead $ADR variable removed; referenced non-existent ad/ad.rules
      directory, removed from MD5_FILES glob (internals.conf)
[Fix] Duplicate MD5_FILES definition removed from apf; clobbered the
      correct definition in internals.conf which includes $RABP (apf)
[Fix] logrotate.d.apf postrotate removed; killall -HUP rsyslogd is
      irrelevant since APF writes its log directly via eout(), not
      through syslog (logrotate.d.apf)
[Fix] bt.rules: "Block Traffic With Invalid Flags" comment corrected to
      "Block INVALID connection states and unusual TCP options" (bt.rules)
[Fix] bt.rules: "p2p networks" comment corrected to "p2p ports"; dead
      service names (WinMX, Napster, Kazaa, etc.) removed (bt.rules)
[Fix] vnetgen exit code: SET_VNET=0 now exits 0 (disabled is not an error)
      instead of exit 1 (vnetgen)
[New] sysctl.rules: added comments for hardcoded conntrack timeouts (600s
      established, 90s time-wait vs kernel defaults) (sysctl.rules)
[New] sysctl.rules: added comment for unconditional port range and ICMP
      settings (sysctl.rules)
[New] sysctl.rules: added note that tcp_tw_recycle was removed in kernel
      4.12 (sysctl.rules)
[New] log.rules: added comment explaining LOG_IA purpose and LOG_DROP
      dependency above the conditional (log.rules)
[Fix] vnetgen.def typos: "defined" → "define" (2 occurrences),
      "iptable" → "iptables" (vnet/vnetgen.def)
[Fix] vnetgen.def invalid example IP 1.0.1.0.1 → RFC 5737 192.0.2.1
      (vnet/vnetgen.def)
[Fix] "line-seperated" → "line-separated" in all 4 trust rules files
      (allow_hosts.rules, deny_hosts.rules, glob_allow.rules,
      glob_deny.rules)
[Fix] multicast.networks: dead MBone URL removed, per-block comments
      collapsed to brief summary, IANA URL upgraded to HTTPS
[Fix] reserved.networks: "Unassigned/reserved" label → "Special-purpose /
      non-routable", IANA URL upgraded to HTTPS
[Fix] private.networks: faqs.org RFC mirror replaced with rfc-editor.org
      canonical URL
[Change] .ca.def TCR_PASS/TCR_PORTS split from one line to two for
      consistency (.ca.def)
[Change] DEVEL_MODE comment compressed from 3 to 2 lines (conf.apf, .ca.def)
[Change] USE_IPV6 comment compressed from 5 to 3 lines (conf.apf, .ca.def)
[Change] SET_VERBOSE comment rewritten: fixed tense, compressed from 4 to
      2 lines (conf.apf, .ca.def)
[Change] SET_FASTLOAD note (e) added: DEVEL_MODE bypasses snapshot
      (conf.apf, .ca.def)
[Change] SET_VNET comment: hardcoded /etc/apf path replaced with
      $INSTALL_PATH; IPv6 limitation note added to .ca.def (conf.apf,
      .ca.def)
[Change] SET_EXPIRE comment clarified: "equiv. seconds" replaced with
      concrete example "10 min = 600s" (conf.apf, .ca.def)
[Change] VF_ROUTE comment: redundant "IFACE_*" replaced with explicit
      "IFACE_UNTRUSTED and IFACE_TRUSTED" (conf.apf, .ca.def)
[Change] RAB intro compressed from 7 lines to 3 lines (conf.apf, .ca.def)
[Change] RAB_LOG_HIT/RAB_LOG_TRIP: verbose LOG_DROP override sentence
      compressed to "LOG_DROP=1 overrides this" (conf.apf, .ca.def)
[Change] SYSCTL_TCP_NOSACK: verbose duplicate CVE block replaced with
      brief cross-reference to BLK_TCP_SACK_PANIC (conf.apf, .ca.def)
[Change] SYSCTL_ROUTE: added note about IPv6 forwarding effect when
      USE_IPV6=1 (conf.apf, .ca.def)
[Change] DLIST_PHP: removed "first and only" marketing copy
      (conf.apf, .ca.def)
[Change] DLIST_ECNSHAME: removed "clueless" editorial language, compressed
      from 7 to 3 lines (conf.apf, .ca.def)
[Fix] Stale variable references in conf.apf comments: USE_RD changed to
      DLIST_RESERVED (BLK_RESNET), USE_ECNSHAME changed to DLIST_ECNSHAME
      (SYSCTL_ECN) (conf.apf, .ca.def)
[Fix] PKT_SANITY_FUDP comment corrected: UDP can fragment at IP layer;
      changed from "no UDP packets should ever be fragmented" to "uncommon
      in typical server traffic" (conf.apf, .ca.def)
[Fix] TCP_STOP/UDP_STOP/ALL_STOP option descriptions corrected: removed
      unsupported "TCP/IP default" claims, fixed "a icmp" to "an ICMP",
      added missing PROHIBIT option to TCP_STOP and ALL_STOP
      (conf.apf, .ca.def)
[Fix] SYSCTL_SYN comment corrected: code raises SYN backlog to 4096, not
      lowers it; changed to "lowering retry counts and increasing SYN
      backlog capacity" (conf.apf, .ca.def)
[Fix] SET_REFRESH comment corrected: describes trust chain refresh
      (TALLOW/TDENY/TGALLOW/TGDENY), not full static rule reload
      (conf.apf, .ca.def)
[Fix] LOG_DROP comment clarified: "filtered" changed to "dropped/rejected"
      (conf.apf, .ca.def)
[Fix] BLK_PORTS garbled sentence rewritten to clear English
      (conf.apf, .ca.def)
[Fix] Dead MBone URL removed from BLK_MCATNET comment (conf.apf, .ca.def)
[Fix] LOG_TARGET: ULOG marked deprecated, NFLOG noted as modern
      alternative (conf.apf, .ca.def)
[Fix] 9 typos/grammar fixes across conf.apf and .ca.def: assignement to
      assignment, by-pass to bypass, hand-shake to handshake, whom to who,
      as so to/so as to, can be used scale/used to scale, i.e:/i.e.,
      too/to (LOG_LEVEL), first-person removed from LOG_LEVEL
[Change] .ca.def LOG_IA comment updated with LOG_DROP dependency note
      matching conf.apf (.ca.def)
[Change] .ca.def SYSCTL_CONNTRACK adaptive variables now have individual
      comments matching conf.apf (.ca.def)
[Change] README section 6 rewritten: dead forums.rfxnetworks.com reference
      removed, support@r-fx.org removed, GitHub repository URL added
      (README, README.md)
[Change] README section 5 license email unified from ryan@r-fx.org to
      ryan@rfxn.com (README, README.md)
[Fix] head() banner email changed from apf@rfxn.com to proj@rfxn.com
      matching all other contact references (apf)
[Fix] README GRE section corrected "encrypted or encapsulated" to
      "encapsulated point-to-point"; GRE provides encapsulation only, not
      encryption (README, README.md)
[Fix] README DLIST_RESERVED description corrected from "ARIN" to "IANA";
      reserved networks list covers globally unassigned space, not just
      North America (README, README.md)
[Fix] README advanced trust examples replaced real public IPs (24.202.x.x)
      with RFC 5737 documentation addresses (198.51.100.x) and personal
      hostname ryanm.dynip.org with RFC 2606 myhost.example.com
      (README, README.md)
[Fix] README backup path example epoch corrected from 1708456789 (2024) to
      1771538400 (2026) matching the DDMMYY portion 190226 (README, README.md)
[New] README installation section: DEVEL_MODE="1" default behavior warning
      added after install completion paragraph (README, README.md)
[Change] README ipset_type description expanded: "hash:ip for single
      addresses, hash:net for CIDR blocks" (README, README.md)
[Change] README section 3 preamble compressed from 33 lines to 9; removed
      redundant prose about config philosophy (README, README.md)
[Change] README section 3.3 RAB converted from Option:/Description: format
      to concise variable-first format matching section 3.1 (README)
[Change] README section 4 CLI explanations tightened; removed restatements
      of information already in the usage table (README, README.md)
[Change] README sections 3.6/3.7/3.8 Option:/Description: labels converted
      to variable-first format for consistency (README)
[Change] README feature list: removed vague "3rd party add-on projects"
      entry that was unexplained (README, README.md)
[Change] README.md regenerated from updated README with proper Markdown
      formatting: anchor-linked TOC, fenced code blocks, Markdown tables,
      inline code (README.md)
[Change] README section 1 introduction compressed; three filtering type
      explanations reduced from verbose paragraphs to concise summaries
      (README, README.md)
[Change] README section 3.1 compressed from Option:/Description: format to
      concise variable-first format; port filtering variables grouped into
      scannable list (README, README.md)
[Change] README section 3.2 TCP_STOP/UDP_STOP/ALL_STOP verbose narrative
      replaced with comparison table; PKT_SANITY, TOS, and TCR descriptions
      tightened (README, README.md)
[New] README sections 3.9 (Remote Block Lists), 3.10 (Logging & Control),
      3.11 (Implicit Blocking) documenting DLIST_*, LOG_*, BLK_* variables
      (README, README.md)
[New] README section 3.2 expanded with Kernel Tuning summary covering
      SYSCTL_* variables (README, README.md)
[New] README section 4.1 expanded with SET_EXPIRE, SET_REFRESH,
      SET_REFRESH_MD5, SET_TRIM trust system controls (README, README.md)
[New] README section 3.1 expanded with EG_DROP_CMD user/app filtering
      documentation (README, README.md)
[Fix] README ipset.rules format corrected from pipe-separated 4-field to
      colon-separated 5-field (name:flow:ipset_type:log:file_or_url)
      matching actual file header (README, README.md)
[Fix] README gre.rules description corrected from delimited data file to
      bash script with role variable and create_gretun() function calls
      (README, README.md)
[Fix] README fabricated section 4.4 (Dynamic Trust Files) removed;
      dyn_allow_hosts.rules and dyn_deny_hosts.rules do not exist in the
      codebase (README, README.md)
[Fix] README installation section corrected docs to doc matching
      install.sh mkdir path (README, README.md)
[Change] README section 4.2 now documents USE_RGT toggle for enabling
      automatic global trust file downloads (README, README.md)
[New] README.md Markdown version for GitHub rendering (README.md)
[Change] README expanded with Docker compat, ipset, GRE tunnel, and IPv6
      documentation; grammar and structure fixes throughout (README)
[Change] help() output updated with --ipset-update, --gre-up, --gre-down,
      --gre-status options (functions.apf)
[New] External INPUT/OUTPUT rule preservation in DOCKER_COMPAT mode;
      save_external_baseline() captures non-APF rules before flush,
      restore_external_baseline() replays them after flush; protects
      Docker Swarm, kube-proxy, and Calico CNI rules from being
      destroyed during APF start/restart/stop (functions.apf)
[New] Docker compat external INPUT preservation tests: 3 tests covering
      start, flush, and restart scenarios with simulated Docker Swarm
      INPUT rule (tests/20-docker-compat.bats)
[Change] DOCKER_COMPAT conf.apf comment updated to document INPUT/OUTPUT
      preservation alongside FORWARD and nat (conf.apf)
[New] Docker/container chain preservation mode (DOCKER_COMPAT); when enabled,
      flush() only removes APF-owned chains, preserving Docker, containerd,
      Kubernetes, and Podman chains in FORWARD and nat table. Fast load and
      snapshot save automatically disabled in compat mode to prevent
      iptables-restore from overwriting external chains (conf.apf,
      functions.apf, apf, .ca.def)
[New] flush_apf_chains() surgical flush function; removes only known APF
      chains from filter table, flushes mangle PREROUTING/POSTROUTING,
      resets INPUT/OUTPUT policies while leaving FORWARD policy and nat/raw
      tables untouched (functions.apf)
[New] Docker compat test suite: 10 tests covering chain preservation across
      start/flush/restart, nuclear flush default, fast load skip, mangle vs
      nat behavior (tests/20-docker-compat.bats)
[Fix] flush_apf_chains() IPv6 chain list missing PHP, DSHIELD, SDROP;
      these dual-stack chains (created via ipt -N) were cleaned from IPv4
      but left as orphans in ip6tables when DOCKER_COMPAT=1 and USE_IPV6=1,
      causing -N errors on subsequent start (functions.apf)
[Fix] GRE eval command injection: create_gretun() no longer uses eval to
      build the tunnel command; replaced with direct $ip tunnel add using
      if/else for the optional key flag (gretunnel.sh)
[Fix] allow_hosts()/deny_hosts() glob expansion: all 8 for-in-$(cat) loops
      converted to while IFS= read -r with process substitution, eliminating
      glob expansion risk on trust file entries (functions.apf)
[Fix] DLIST disabled regression: dlist_php(), dlist_dshield(), and
      dlist_spamhaus() else branches now clear the rules file when the feature
      is disabled; previously restored from backup, contradicting operator
      intent to disable the list (functions.apf)
[Fix] --gre-down leaves stale firewall chains: gre_teardown() now flushes
      and deletes GRE_IN/GRE_OUT chains and removes INPUT/OUTPUT jumps;
      previously only destroyed tunnel interfaces (gretunnel.sh)
[Fix] --gre-up idempotent: gre_init() now guards chain creation with
      existence check; previously failed with "chain already exists" when
      called on a running firewall (gretunnel.sh)
[Fix] --ipset-update mutex: the --ipset-update CLI path now calls
      mutex_lock() to prevent racing with concurrent apf -r (apf)
[Fix] GRE tunnel creation exit codes: $ip tunnel add and $ip link set
      return codes now checked; failure aborts with error message instead
      of continuing to add firewall rules for non-existent interfaces
      (gretunnel.sh)
[Fix] GRE endpoint validation: create_gretun() now uses valid_ip_cidr()
      instead of valid_host() for routefrom/routeto; GRE requires IP
      addresses, not hostnames which the kernel silently rejects
      (gretunnel.sh)
[Fix] GRE key validation: tunnel key now validated as integer; non-numeric
      values rejected with error message before reaching the kernel
      (gretunnel.sh)
[New] MCAST6 NDP RETURN test assertion: verifies ICMPv6 RETURN exemptions
      in MCAST6 chain that protect NDP from multicast blocking
      (tests/06-ipv6.bats)
[New] DLIST disabled no-chain test: verifies DLIST_*=0 clears rules files
      and creates no iptables chain (tests/19-dlist.bats)
[Fix] GRE protocol 47 test assertions widened for old iptables on Ubuntu
      12.04 which displays -p 47 instead of -p gre (tests/18-gre.bats)
[Fix] DShield /24 host inflation: dlist_dshield() no longer appends /24
      to individual host IPs from the DShield feed; entries are now written
      as-is, preventing collateral blocking of 256 addresses per host
      (functions.apf)
[Fix] dlist download resilience: dlist_dshield(), dlist_php(), and
      dlist_spamhaus() now backup rules files before download and restore
      from backup on failure; previously a failed download left rules files
      empty, losing all existing entries (functions.apf)
[Change] dlist parse-time validation: dlist_dshield(), dlist_php(), and
      dlist_spamhaus() now validate entries via valid_ip_cidr() during
      parsing; garbage from corrupted downloads is rejected before writing
      to rules files (functions.apf)
[Fix] conf.apf and .ca.def DShield description corrected from "top
      networks" to "top hosts" to match actual feed content (conf.apf,
      .ca.def)
[New] DLIST chain-loading test suite: 11 tests covering DSHIELD/PHP/SDROP
      chain creation, DROP rules, INPUT attachment, backup/restore
      resilience, and invalid entry rejection (tests/19-dlist.bats)
[Change] Subsystem definition file naming normalized: gre.conf renamed to
      gre.rules for consistency with ipset.rules and other .rules files;
      all references updated (gretunnel.sh, conf.apf, .ca.def, tests)
[Change] ipset.rules and gre.rules headers now cross-reference their
      conf.apf config sections for discoverability
[Fix] importconf now preserves gre.rules during upgrades; previously
      user tunnel definitions were lost on upgrade (importconf)
[New] GRE tunnel support: encapsulated point-to-point links with dedicated
      GRE_IN/GRE_OUT chains, protocol 47 rules, and per-tunnel interface
      accept rules. USE_GRE config toggle, gre.rules definition file,
      create_gretun()/destroy_gretun()/gre_init()/gre_flush()/gre_teardown()/
      gre_status() lifecycle functions, --gre-up/--gre-down/--gre-status CLI
      options, auto-MTU calculation, keepalive, tunnel key, per-tunnel
      overrides, source/target role routing (conf.apf, internals.conf,
      gretunnel.sh, gre.rules, firewall, functions.apf, apf, .ca.def)
[New] GRE test suite: 14 tests covering tunnel creation, chain structure,
      protocol 47 rules, interface rules, addresses, MTU, IP routing,
      disable/enable, flush persistence, teardown, validation
      (tests/18-gre.bats)
[Change] All 10 Dockerfiles and install-apf.sh updated with USE_GRE="0"
      config override for deterministic test behavior
[New] ipset block list support: kernel-level hash tables for O(1) IP matching.
      USE_IPSET config toggle, ipset.rules definition file, ipset_load()/
      ipset_update()/ipset_flush() lifecycle functions, --ipset-update CLI
      option for cron hot-reload, cron.d.apf_ipset cron job, ip_set/xt_set
      module loading, check_deps() ipset warning (conf.apf, internals.conf,
      functions.apf, bt.rules, apf, install.sh, ipset.rules, cron.d.apf_ipset)
[New] ipset test suite: 12 tests covering set creation, chain attachment,
      match rules, hot-reload, flush cleanup, empty/CIDR blocklists, logging
      (tests/17-ipset.bats)
[Change] All 10 Dockerfiles updated with ipset package and USE_IPSET="0"
      config override for deterministic test behavior
[Change] CentOS 6 and Ubuntu 12.04 added to GitHub Actions CI matrix
      (.github/workflows/smoke-test.yml)
[Change] Makefile test-all and test-all-parallel targets now include
      centos6 and ubuntu1204 (tests/Makefile)
[Fix] ipset entry count assertions use portable member counting for
      old ipset v6.x compatibility on CentOS 6 and Ubuntu 12.04
      (tests/17-ipset.bats)
[Fix] importconf now preserves ipset.rules during upgrades (importconf)
[Fix] MCAST6 chain now exempts NDP ICMPv6 types 133-136 before blocking
      ff00::/8; previously BLK_MCATNET=1 with USE_IPV6=1 broke IPv6
      neighbor discovery by dropping multicast NDP packets (bt.rules)
[Fix] SSH helper removed dead rule with mutually exclusive --syn and
      --state ESTABLISHED,RELATED flags that could never match (firewall)
[Fix] SSH helper removed spurious UDP ACCEPT rule — SSH is TCP-only;
      rule incorrectly opened UDP on the SSH port (firewall)
[Fix] Interface validation error messages now reference the specific
      failing interface instead of the entire interface list (firewall)
[Change] ipset chain wiring uses ipt4() helper instead of raw $IPT for
      consistency with dual-stack convention (functions.apf)
[Change] Loopback rules use ipt() helper and remove redundant 0/0 source/
      destination match (firewall)
[Fix] Advanced trust syntax now rejects entries with unrecognized flow,
      direction, or protocol fields instead of passing them as raw
      iptables flags — prevents malformed trust entries from injecting
      arbitrary arguments (functions.apf)
[Fix] refresh() temp files now use mktemp instead of PID-based naming,
      preventing symlink attack vectors (functions.apf)
[Fix] dlist_ecnshame() download now filters for IP-shaped content and
      strips comments, matching all other dlist download functions
      (functions.apf)
[Change] All dlist_*_hosts() chain-loading functions, dnet(), expirebans(),
      and refresh() converted from for-in-cat to while-read loops,
      eliminating glob expansion risk on trust file entries (functions.apf)
[Fix] valid_host() IPv4 now delegates to valid_ip_cidr() for octet range
      validation; rejects invalid addresses like 999.1.2.3 and masks > /32
      (functions.apf)
[Fix] valid_host() IPv6 CIDR mask now validated <= 128; rejects invalid
      masks like /999 (functions.apf)
[Fix] valid_host() IPv6 regex accepts compressed forms starting with ::
      (e.g. ::1, ::/0); leading hextet changed from {1,4} to {0,4}
      (functions.apf)
[Fix] Fast load with USE_IPV6=1 falls through to full load when
      ip6tables-restore is missing instead of silently succeeding
      with only IPv4 rules loaded (apf)
[Fix] IPv6 tests skip gracefully when ip6tables kernel module is unavailable;
      adds ip6tables_available() helper and per-test skip guards across 6
      test files for GH Actions CentOS 7 compatibility; fixed BATS subprocess
      isolation issue with variable-based skip (tests/helpers/assert-iptables.bash,
      tests/04-trust-system.bats, tests/06-ipv6.bats, tests/08-fastload.bats,
      tests/09-flush-cleanup.bats, tests/11-advanced-trust.bats,
      tests/16-dependency-check.bats)
[New] Deep legacy test targets: CentOS 6 (vault.centos.org) and Ubuntu 12.04
      (old-releases.ubuntu.com) reintroduced as manual test targets with
      Dockerfiles, run-tests.sh, and Makefile deep-legacy group
      (tests/Dockerfile.centos6, tests/Dockerfile.ubuntu1204)
[Fix] CentOS 6 Dockerfile: added iptables-ipv6 package for ip6tables support
[Fix] Packet sanity test patterns widened to handle third iptables output
      format (tcpflags: 0xNN/0xNN) found on very old legacy systems
      (tests/07-packet-sanity.bats)
[Fix] apf -l dependency check test uses timeout to prevent hang when editor
      (vi) is present in container (tests/16-dependency-check.bats)
[Change] Removed Dockerfiles for Ubuntu 16.04 and Ubuntu 18.04; repos are
         no longer accessible. Test matrix aligned to CI targets: Debian 12,
         CentOS 7, Rocky 8/9, Ubuntu 20.04/22.04/24.04. Rocky 10 retained
         for manual testing (tests/Makefile, tests/run-tests.sh)
[Fix] list() predictable temp file replaced with mktemp; PID-based
      $INSTALL_PATH/.iptrules.$$ changed to mktemp with XXXXXX suffix;
      all file references now quoted (functions.apf)
[New] Centralized dependency checking via check_deps(); validates iptables,
      ip, modprobe, ip6tables (critical) and wget, iptables-save/restore,
      diff (warning) before firewall start with OS-aware install hints
      (functions.apf, apf)
[Change] Ad-hoc ip/ifconfig existence check removed from firewall; superseded
         by check_deps() with correct -z test instead of buggy -f test
         (firewall)
[Change] Ad-hoc wget/DLIST hard abort removed from firewall; downgraded to
         warning in check_deps() since dlist_* functions handle missing wget
         gracefully (firewall)
[New] Dependency check test file (16-dependency-check.bats) with 8 tests
      covering critical/optional detection, install hints, and non-start
      commands bypassing checks (tests/)
[Fix] Fast load error handling: iptables-restore and ip6tables-restore exit
      codes now checked; corrupted or incompatible snapshots fall through to
      full load instead of reporting success with no rules applied (apf)
[Fix] Fast load IPv6 snapshot gap: when USE_IPV6=1 but no IPv6 snapshot
      exists (first boot after enabling IPv6), partial IPv4-only fast load
      is now detected, flushed, and falls through to full load (apf)
[Fix] .ca.def SET_REFRESH_MD5 description corrected from "value in minutes"
      to "value 1 to enable, 0 to disable" matching conf.apf (.ca.def)
[New] IPv6 trust syntax documentation added to deny_hosts.rules with
      bracket notation examples matching allow_hosts.rules (deny_hosts.rules)
[Fix] head() email domain standardized from @rfxn.org to @rfxn.com (apf)
[Change] help() output updated: -a/-d options now show IP/IPv6/CIDR/FQDN
      instead of IP/FQDN (functions.apf)
[Change] Error messages in cli_trust() and cli_trust_remove() now mention
      IPv6 addresses explicitly (functions.apf)
[Change] Fast load eout message now includes iptables backend type
      (legacy/nf_tables) for easier troubleshooting (apf)
[Fix] conf.apf and .ca.def comment typos: subsiquent→subsequent,
      inital→initial, allot→a lot, etc..→etc., your→you're,
      HTTP→HTTPS in comment URLs (conf.apf, .ca.def)
[Change] Test suite performance: consolidated redundant flush+start cycles in
      08-fastload.bats (3 IPv6 tests merged into 1), 09-flush-cleanup.bats
      (5 flush tests merged into 1), and 11-advanced-trust.bats (17 per-test
      flush+start cycles replaced with single setup_file() load)
[Change] APF pre-installed during Docker build; test files use fast reset-apf.sh
      helper instead of re-running install.sh (~2.5s saved per test file)
[New] Parallel test targets: make -C tests test-all-parallel runs all OS targets
      concurrently using half available cores
[Change] Makefile moved from project root to tests/ directory; use
      make -C tests test (tests/Makefile)
[Change] GHA workflow uses docker/build-push-action with buildx layer caching
      for faster CI builds (.github/workflows/smoke-test.yml)
[Change] Deleted stale GHA failure files from pre-Phase 35 test run
      (tests/centos7.github.failure, tests/ubuntu2204.github.failure)
[Change] wget download functions no longer force IPv4-only transport; removed
      -4 flag from all 7 $WGET calls to allow dual-stack connectivity via
      happy eyeballs; IPv6-only hosts can now download blocklists
      (functions.apf)
[Fix] importconf cross-test contamination; trust file entries from prior test
      runs no longer persist across reinstalls in test suite
      (tests/helpers/install-apf.sh)
[Fix] sysctl log_martians test false positive; previously accepted both 0 and 1
      (always passing); now verifies write actually takes effect or skips when
      Docker kernel ignores sysctl writes (tests/12-sysctl.bats)
[Fix] OUTPUT policy test false positive; replaced fragile tail/grep with
      assert_chain_policy helper (tests/02-chain-verification.bats)
[Change] Per-test teardown() added to test files 06, 11, 13 to prevent dirty
      state from leaking between tests on mid-test failure
      (tests/06-ipv6.bats, tests/11-advanced-trust.bats,
      tests/13-refresh-expiry.bats)
[New] Fast load restore path test; verifies iptables-restore from snapshot
      actually restores chains on second start (tests/08-fastload.bats)
[New] RAB test file (15-rab.bats) with 7 tests covering chain structure,
      portscan rules, and logging; gracefully skips when xt_recent kernel
      module unavailable in Docker (tests/15-rab.bats)
[Change] Backtick command substitutions modernized to $() across all files:
      functions.apf (97), cports.common (36), apf (8), firewall (9),
      bt.rules (4), vnetgen (3), main.vnet (2), importconf (2),
      install.sh (4) — 165 total replacements
[Fix] lgate_mac() log prefix typo "FORIGN" corrected to "FOREIGN"
      (functions.apf)
[Change] Variable quoting hardened across critical paths: eout(), trim(),
      cli_trust(), cli_trust_remove(), status(), devm() file operations
      (functions.apf)
[Change] Trust file local-address checks quote $HOST, $i, $PIP and file
      path arguments (functions.apf)
[Change] apf entry point: quoted $LOG_APF, $DS_HOSTS, $DENY_HOSTS,
      $ALLOW_HOSTS in touch/chmod/test operations (apf)
[Fix] vnetgen: [ -f "$ip" ] semantic error changed to [ -n "$ip" ] and
      [ -z "$ip" ] for correct command-availability detection (vnetgen)
[Change] vnetgen: quoted $IF, $NET, $anet, $iface, $IFACE_TRUSTED and
      all touch/chmod/source paths (vnetgen)
[Change] firewall: quoted $i in trusted interface grep (firewall)
[Change] bt.rules: quoted $IG_TCP_CPORTS in IDENT port check (bt.rules)
[Fix] cli_trust() duplicate check matched comment lines, causing false
      "already exists" after apf -u/-a cycle; now filters comments and
      restores whole-word matching (functions.apf)
[Fix] IPv6 trust tests missing USE_IPV6=1 in test setup; added to
      04-trust-system.bats and 11-advanced-trust.bats
[Change] URL filename extraction in 7 download functions replaced backtick
         tr/grep/tail pipeline with ${URL##*/} parameter expansion
         (functions.apf)
[Fix] unquoted cd $INSTALL_PATH in 7 download function cleanup paths; now
      quoted as cd "$INSTALL_PATH" (functions.apf)
[Change] conf.apf GA_URL/GD_URL example URLs updated from http:// to
         https:// matching all other DLIST URLs (conf.apf)
[Fix] trim() log message typo "triming" corrected to "trimming"
      (functions.apf)
[Change] internals.conf 6 backtick command substitutions modernized to $()
         syntax (internals.conf)
[Change] cli_trust() two-pass grep consolidated to single grep -Fl call
         (functions.apf)
[Change] dnet() filename extraction replaced backtick tr/tail pipeline with
         ${FILE##*/} parameter expansion (functions.apf)
[New] IPv6 fragmented UDP blocking; FRAG_UDP6 chain uses -m frag --fragmore
      to match IPv6 fragment extension headers; includes RAB logging and
      sanity flags matching IPv4 FRAG_UDP behavior (bt.rules)
[Fix] refresh() IPv4-only load check; only checked $IPT for TALLOW chain;
      now falls back to $IP6T when USE_IPV6=1 so IPv6-only rule sets are
      correctly detected (functions.apf)
[New] IPv6 trust syntax documentation added to glob_allow.rules and
      glob_deny.rules matching allow_hosts.rules format (glob rules)
[Fix] hardcoded /sbin/route replaced with command -v route for portable
      detection; route binary at /usr/sbin/route on RHEL 8+/Debian 12+
      (firewall)
[Fix] get_ports IPv6 parsing; rev|cut -d: split on IPv6 colons producing
      wrong ports; replaced with sed 's/.*://'; ::1 loopback now filtered
      alongside 127.* (get_ports)
[Change] list() editor discovery uses command -v loop instead of hardcoded
         paths /usr/bin/pico, /usr/bin/nano, /bin/vi (functions.apf)
[Fix] firewall dead head command removed from CNF error path (firewall)
[Fix] expirebans() flock deadlock; spawned $INSTALL_PATH/apf -u as child process
      which attempted to acquire the same flock held by parent, causing 60s hang
      then silent failure; changed to direct cli_trust_remove() call
      (functions.apf)
[Fix] expirebans() sed not anchored; unanchored pattern \%$ip%d caused
      10.0.0.1 removal to also delete 10.0.0.10; added ^ anchor and \b word
      boundary (functions.apf)
[Fix] cli_trust_remove() error suppression; ipt_for_host "|| true" masked IPv6
      errors leaving $IPT_H in stale state; now returns error with message when
      USE_IPV6 not enabled (functions.apf)
[Fix] cli_trust_remove() first-match-only rule deletion; INPUT/OUTPUT cleanup
      used single awk+delete which only removed first matching rule; converted
      to tac + loop pattern matching TALLOW/TDENY for complete cleanup
      (functions.apf)
[Change] cli_trust_remove() modernized backtick subshells to $() syntax
         (functions.apf)
[Change] Blocklist chains (PHP, DSHIELD, SDROP) converted from $IPT to ipt()
         for dual-stack chain creation/attachment; per-entry rules use
         ipt_for_host() routing with $IPT_H/$ANY_ADDR (functions.apf)
[Change] ECN shame list converted from $IPT to ipt_for_host() routing for
         IPv6-capable mangle rules (functions.apf)
[Change] dnet() deny network loader converted from ipt4() to ipt_for_host()
         routing; IPv6 deny networks now blocked when USE_IPV6=1
         (functions.apf)
[New] Conntrack hash table sizing via SYSCTL_CONNTRACK_BUCKETS; writes to
      /sys/module/nf_conntrack/parameters/hashsize when set (sysctl.rules)
[New] Adaptive conntrack scaling; SYSCTL_CONNTRACK_ADAPTIVE auto-scales
      conntrack_max when usage exceeds 80% threshold, capped at
      SYSCTL_CONNTRACK_HIGH ceiling (sysctl.rules, conf.apf)
[New] nf_conntrack_helper disabled by default to reduce ALG attack surface
      (CVE-2013-6390, CVE-2019-8956) (sysctl.rules)
[Fix] IPv6 sysctl per-interface scope; accept_source_route and
      accept_redirects now set on both /conf/all/ and /conf/$IFACE_UNTRUSTED/
      matching IPv4 hardening pattern; previously only set on /conf/all/
      (sysctl.rules)
[Fix] IPv6 route flush added; /proc/sys/net/ipv6/route/flush now triggered
      alongside IPv4 flush when USE_IPV6=1 (sysctl.rules)
[Fix] IPv6 plain trust addresses silently dropped; allow_hosts()/deny_hosts()
      used grep -v ":" which excluded all IPv6 entries from Loop 1 plain IP
      processing; changed to grep -v "=" to filter only advanced syntax
      (functions.apf)
[New] IPv6 advanced trust bracket notation; bracketed IPv6 addresses in
      trust syntax (e.g., d=22:s=[2001:db8::1]) protect colons from the
      field delimiter parser; trust_protect_ipv6()/trust_restore_ipv6()
      helpers handle bracket escaping transparently (functions.apf)
[Fix] IPv6 sanity chains missing RAB integration; IN_SANITY6/OUT_SANITY6
      and PZERO6 now include $RAB_SANITY_FLAGS and RAB_LOG_HIT logging,
      matching IPv4 IN_SANITY/OUT_SANITY behavior (bt.rules)
[Change] RAB trip rules converted from $IPT to ipt() for IPv6 dual-stack;
         xt_recent tracks both IPv4 and IPv6 addresses (firewall)
[Change] RABPSCAN chain converted from $IPT to ipt() for IPv6 dual-stack;
         DNS whitelist now routes IPv4/IPv6 nameservers via ipt_for_host()
         (firewall)
[Change] VNET IPv4-only limitation documented in conf.apf; IPv6 uses
         neither interface aliasing nor colon-safe filenames (conf.apf)
[New] IPv6 trust syntax documentation with bracket notation examples
      (allow_hosts.rules)
[New] BATS smoke test suite with Docker and network namespace support;
      14 test files (180 tests) covering install/CLI, chains, ports, trust,
      multi-interface, IPv6, packet sanity, fast load, flush, validation,
      advanced trust syntax, sysctl, refresh/expiry, and install paths (tests/)
[New] Multi-OS Docker test matrix: Debian 12, CentOS 7, Rocky 8/9,
      Ubuntu 20.04/22.04/24.04; with Dockerfiles for CentOS 6, Rocky 10,
      Ubuntu 16.04/18.04 (tests/Dockerfile.*)
[New] Cross-distro netcat portability helper for nc/ncat differences
      (tests/helpers/detect-nc.sh)
[New] Backend-portable iptables assertions using iptables -S; supports both
      nft and legacy backends (tests/helpers/assert-iptables.bash)
[New] Makefile with per-OS test targets, test-modern/test-legacy/test-all
      groups (Makefile)
[New] GitHub Actions CI matrix across 7 OS targets (.github/workflows/)
[Change] run-tests.sh supports --os flag for distro selection (tests/)
[Fix] flush() inoperative on nft backend; /proc/net/ip_tables_names absent on
      iptables-nft causes flush loops to skip entirely, leaving all rules in
      place after apf -f; now falls back to hardcoded table list
      (functions.apf)
[Change] which replaced with command -v (POSIX builtin) for all 16 binary
         discovery variables in internals.conf
[Change] mutex_lock()/mutex_unlock() rewritten with flock for atomic kernel-level
         locking; eliminates TOCTOU race in polling lock (functions.apf)
[New] -v|--version CLI option outputs version number (apf, functions.apf)
[New] systemd service unit (apf.service); install.sh prefers systemd over SysV
      init when /run/systemd/system detected (install.sh)
[Change] apf.init modernized: removed RHEL-specific /etc/rc.d/init.d/functions
         dependency, uses $INSTALL_PATH, added status command (apf.init)
[Change] install.sh now sed-replaces $INSTALL_PATH in init script and systemd
         service when non-default path used (install.sh)
[Change] get_ports uses ss as primary with netstat fallback; netstat removed
         from modern distros (extras/get_ports)
[New] IPv6 PKT_SANITY: IN_SANITY6/OUT_SANITY6 chains with TCP flag checks,
      INVALID state blocking, and PZERO6 port-zero filtering (bt.rules)
[New] IPv6 multicast blocking; MCAST6 chain blocks ff00::/8 when
      BLK_MCATNET=1 and USE_IPV6=1 (bt.rules)
[New] $IP6TS/$IP6TR variables for ip6tables-save/ip6tables-restore discovery
      (internals.conf)
[New] IPv6 fast load save/restore; ip6tables snapshot saved as .apf6.restore
      alongside IPv4 snapshot, restored on fast load when USE_IPV6=1 (apf)
[Change] list() now shows both IPv4 and IPv6 rules when USE_IPV6=1
      (functions.apf)
[Change] flush() fast save now includes ip6tables snapshot when USE_IPV6=1
      (functions.apf)
[Change] refresh() now extracts and preserves IPv6 trust addresses from
      ip6tables-save during trust chain refresh; uses ipt() for chain flushes
      (functions.apf)
[New] ipt_for_host() helper routes iptables commands to correct table based on
      host address family; detects IPv6 by ':' presence, sets $IPT_H/$ANY_ADDR
[Fix] trust system IPv6 support; cli_trust(), cli_trust_remove(), allow_hosts(),
      deny_hosts() now detect IPv6 addresses and apply rules to ip6tables with
      ::/0 instead of incorrectly routing them through iptables with 0/0
[Fix] .localaddrs6 checked alongside .localaddrs in all trust functions to
      prevent local IPv6 addresses from being added to trust system
[New] valid_host() and valid_ip_cidr() input validation functions for trust
      system operations
[New] ipt()/ipt4()/ipt6() dual-stack iptables helper functions; ipt() runs
      both IPv4 and IPv6 when USE_IPV6=1, ipt4()/ipt6() for protocol-specific
[New] IPv6 kernel module loading when USE_IPV6=1; ip6_tables, ip6table_filter,
      nf_conntrack_ipv6
[New] nft backend detection; iptables-save snapshot includes backend marker
      (.apf.restore.backend) for safe restore across nft/legacy iptables
[Fix] RAB_PSCAN_LEVEL always-true condition; || changed to && (firewall)
[Fix] EG_DROP_CMD dead code; comparison to "1" changed to non-empty check
      (cports.common)
[Fix] missing $ prefix on LOG_DROP variable reference (cports.common)
[Fix] RESV_DNS_DROP duplicate ACCEPT rules removed from DNS filtering loop
      (firewall)
[Fix] fastload message incorrectly stated "1h" when threshold is 12h (apf)
[Fix] ovars() broken AWK expression rewritten with ${!var} indirect expansion
      (functions.apf)
[Fix] duplicate IPFLOW variable checks corrected to PFLOW in trust parsing
      x6 (functions.apf)
[Fix] cli_trust() now validates HOST input via valid_host() before trust
      operations (functions.apf)
[Fix] sed delimiter hardened to % in cli_trust_remove() and expirebans() to
      prevent metacharacter injection (functions.apf)
[Fix] blocklist integrity validation added via valid_ip_cidr() in all dlist_*
      download functions (functions.apf)
[Fix] unquoted variable expansion in file operations (install.sh, functions.apf)
[Fix] hardcoded /sbin/ip replaced with $ip variable for cross-OS compatibility;
      breaks on RHEL 8+/Ubuntu 20+ where ip is at /usr/sbin/ip (firewall,
      vnetgen)
[Fix] hardcoded /sbin/iptables-save replaced with $IPTS variable
      (functions.apf)
[Fix] 35+ hardcoded /etc/apf/ paths replaced with $INSTALL_PATH across
      download functions, expirebans(), refresh(), cron, temp files, trust
      md5 (functions.apf, apf)
[Fix] all 8 $IP6T calls now include $IPT_FLAGS lock flag; previously skipped
      -w timeout causing potential concurrent modification (functions.apf,
      firewall, bt.rules)
[Fix] IPv6 loopback rules corrected from 0/0 to ::/0 (firewall)
[Fix] SYSCTL_TCP_NOSACK non-empty test corrected to == "1"; setting to "0"
      previously still disabled SACK (sysctl.rules)
[Fix] tcp_tw_recycle guarded behind /proc file existence; removed in kernel
      4.12 (sysctl.rules)
[Fix] 4 duplicate sysctl writes removed: log_martians x2, rp_filter x2,
      accept_source_route x2 (sysctl.rules)
[Fix] conf.apf date typo "2109" corrected to "2019"
[Fix] cli_trust_remove() now validates input via valid_host() (functions.apf)
[Fix] valid_host() IPv6 regex tightened to require colon-separated groups;
      previously accepted invalid strings like "ff" or "::::" (functions.apf)
[Fix] dead variables removed: LSTOP, LACCEPT, TOS_DEF_TOS, DSTOP
      (internals.conf)
[Fix] unused MOD assignment removed from ml() function (functions.apf)
[Fix] duplicate cron.daily conditional collapsed in install.sh
[Fix] $ip usage guarded behind -n check to prevent errors when ip binary
      is absent (internals.conf)
[Fix] vnetgen ifconfig fallback uses interface line detection instead of
      grep Link which fails on modern net-tools (vnetgen)
[Fix] deprecated $[...] arithmetic replaced with $((...)) across all files
[Fix] ipchains check guarded behind kernel 2.4 detection (functions.apf)
[Fix] --cmd-owner runtime detection with graceful skip for kernels that
      removed xt_owner cmd support (cports.common)
[Change] module loading rewritten with modprobe --dry-run for portable
         detection across .ko, .ko.xz, .ko.zst extensions (functions.apf)
[Change] ip route used as primary with route as fallback for interface
         validation (firewall)
[Change] ifconfig made optional; ip command used as primary in VNET
         subsystem (vnetgen, main.vnet)
[Change] which lsmod/rmmod no longer passes redundant absolute paths
         (internals.conf)
[New] ipt()/ipt4()/ipt6() helpers adopted across rule files; protocol-agnostic
      rules now apply to both IPv4 and IPv6 when USE_IPV6=1 (firewall, bt.rules,
      log.rules, functions.apf)
[Change] chain creation, MSS clamping, connection state, default policies,
         helpers (FTP/SSH/Traceroute), logging, P2P, and IDENT rules now use
         ipt() for dual-stack support (firewall, bt.rules, log.rules)
[Change] common drop ports (cdports) now use ipt() for dual-stack blocking
         (functions.apf)
[Change] flush() refactored: default policies use ipt(), table flush loops
         use ipt4/ipt6 with separate proc chain lists (functions.apf)
[Change] cports.common port rules converted to ipt4() with redundant -s 0/0
         removed; true dual-stack port filtering deferred to Phase 10
         (cports.common)
[Change] packet sanity, fragment, multicast, lgate_mac rules converted to
         explicit ipt4() to clarify IPv4-specific intent (bt.rules,
         functions.apf)
[Change] BLK_TCP_SACK_PANIC collapsed from separate $IPT/$IP6T blocks to
         single ipt() call (bt.rules)
[Change] EG_DROP_CMD section converted to ipt4(); redundant -s 0/0 -d 0/0
         removed (cports.common)
[New] IPv6 local address detection; .localaddrs6 generated alongside
      .localaddrs when USE_IPV6=1 (firewall)
[New] IPv6 PROHIBIT chain with icmp6-adm-prohibited reject target (firewall)
[New] ipt_dst()/ipt_src() VNET-aware dual-stack helpers for port filtering;
      IPv4 gets -d/-s $VNET, IPv6 applies without address restriction
      (functions.apf)
[New] ICMPv6 filtering support with IG_ICMPV6_TYPES and EG_ICMPV6_TYPES
      config variables; NDP types 133-136 always permitted (cports.common,
      conf.apf)
[New] IPv6 DNS filtering; nameservers from resolv.conf routed to ipt4/ipt6
      based on address type (firewall)
[Change] trusted interface rules converted to ipt() dual-stack; redundant
         -s 0/0 -d 0/0 removed (firewall)
[Change] TCP/UDP port filtering converted from ipt4 to ipt_dst/ipt_src for
         dual-stack support; IPv6 gets port rules when USE_IPV6=1 (cports.common)
[Change] RESV_DNS_DROP rules converted to ipt4/ipt6 with IPv6 coverage when
         USE_IPV6=1 (firewall)
[Change] cl_cports() clears ICMPv6 variables between VNET iterations
         (functions.apf)
[Fix] SYSCTL_ROUTE else branch removed; previously ENABLED ip_forward,
      bootp_relay, and forwarding when routing protection was off, turning
      server into a router (sysctl.rules)
[Fix] allow_hosts() and deny_hosts() now validate plain IP entries via
      valid_host() before passing to iptables; prevents injection from
      malicious trust file entries (functions.apf)
[Fix] cli_trust_remove() sed pattern anchored with ^ and \b to prevent
      substring matching; 10.0.0.1 no longer removes 10.0.0.10
      (functions.apf)
[Fix] EG_DROP_CMD LOG rule now includes --cmd-owner filter; previously
      logged ALL packets in DEG chain instead of only matched commands
      (cports.common)
[Change] temp directories in download functions use mktemp -d for atomic
         creation; eliminates PID-based predictable paths and TOCTOU race
         (functions.apf)
[Change] DLIST download URLs updated from HTTP to HTTPS for all upstream
         sources: cdn.rfxn.com, spamhaus.org, feeds.dshield.org (conf.apf,
         .ca.def)
[Fix] VER in apf CLI updated from "1.7.6-2" to "2.0.1" (apf)
[Fix] ALL_STOP unconditional override removed from internals.conf; now only
      defaults to DROP when unset by conf.apf (internals.conf)
[Fix] tosroute() uses return instead of break for early exit (functions.apf)
[Fix] EG_DROP_CMD default value changed from space-separated to comma-separated
      to match the tr ',' parser in cports.common (conf.apf)
[Fix] DEVEL_ON timing: fast load now checks DEVEL_MODE directly instead of
      DEVEL_ON which is set after the check point (apf)
[Fix] refresh() APF detection changed from PROHIBIT grep to TALLOW chain;
      works with non-default UDP_STOP settings (functions.apf)
[Fix] refresh() double REFRESH_TEMP flush removed; allow rules no longer
      destroyed before deny rules are loaded (functions.apf)
[Fix] DNS port range corrected from 1023:65535 to 1024:65535 in all DNS
      rules (firewall)
[Fix] BLK_P2P_PORTS duplicate port 6346 removed (conf.apf)
[Fix] .ca.def date typo "2109" corrected to "2019"
[Fix] $TIF undefined variable replaced with $IFACE_TRUSTED in vnetgen;
      SET_ADDIFACE trusted interface exclusion now functional (vnetgen)
[Change] LOG_IA dependency on LOG_DROP documented in conf.apf
[Fix] /etc/init.d/apf hardcoded paths replaced with $INSTALL_PATH/apf -f
      in devm() cron, allow_hosts(), deny_hosts() (functions.apf)
[Fix] importconf copy destinations changed from /etc/apf/ to $INSTALL_PATH/
      (importconf)
[Fix] install.sh copies files before sed to prevent source tree corruption
      on repeated installs; sed only runs when INSTALL_PATH != /etc/apf
[Fix] install.sh uses mkdir -p and validates backup before rm -rf
[Fix] .ca.def hardcoded values (SET_TRIM, TOS_DEF_RANGE, TCR_PORTS,
      SYSCTL_ROUTE, DLIST_RESERVED) converted to $variable imports
[Fix] .ca.def date typo "2109" corrected to "2019"
[New] .ca.def: SYSCTL_CONNTRACK_ADAPTIVE, SYSCTL_CONNTRACK_INCREMENT,
      SYSCTL_CONNTRACK_HIGH, SYSCTL_CONNTRACK_BUCKETS variable imports added
[Change] install.sh rotates apf_log instead of deleting on upgrade
[Change] logrotate.d.apf given proper weekly rotation, compression, and
         postrotate directive
[Fix] valid_ip_cidr() now validates octet ranges (0-255) and CIDR mask
      limit (0-32); previously accepted 999.999.999.999 (functions.apf)
[Fix] valid_host() FQDN regex requires at least one dot; single-label names
      like "localhost" no longer accepted (functions.apf)
[Fix] private.networks updated with RFC 6598 100.64.0.0/10 Carrier-Grade
      NAT range (private.networks)
[Fix] wget exit code checked in all 7 download functions; partial downloads
      no longer processed (functions.apf)
[New] IPv6 sysctl hardening when USE_IPV6=1: disables accept_source_route,
      accept_redirects, accept_ra; disables forwarding when SYSCTL_ROUTE=1
      (sysctl.rules)
